From 84d1851e28e3981da050fb78d96abdc5a49235f9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Marios Trivyzas <matriv@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 25 Jul 2024 12:14:17 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] Fix behavior of LIKE/ILIKE with trailing ESCAPE char

Following PostgreSQL behavior when the pattern for `LIKE/ILIKE`
and `[NOT] LIKE/ILIKE ANY(<array>)` ends with the `ESCAPE` character
an error is thrown. Differation to PostgreSQL behavior comes only with
the case of `'' LIKE '\'` where PostgreSQL returns false instead of
throwing an error, where as CrateDB throws an error also for this case.

- Introduce a `validateRightArg` method to `AnyOperator` which is
  implemented only for the case of LIKE/ILIKE (with or without NOT) and
  validates the pattern.

- Make sure that the error is thrown also in the case of the operators
  getting translated into LuceneQueries (when a table text col is
  indexed).

- Use generics on `AnyOperator` to avoid some unnecessary castings

Fixes: #16350
